messages.message:
Seems like we changed the sort method for AI Hub converse projects.  I used to have them organized by name using a date convention.  Is there any way to change the sort?

Also looks like we can no longer upload folders.  I've attached a zip of the folder that fails.
could the sorting be related to your recent project sidebar changes? @Weiming Wu
could you previously upload the same folder into AI Hub?

r.e. ordering:  real minor detail, but it was annoying since i have accumulated lots of projects across all the amazing demos we've been able to do!

r.e. file upload:  aaah sorry - shouldnt have reported both at the same time.  Seems that my issue was in the folder itself.  One of my files is a weird format i didnt catch.  It would be nice if we called that out though... "your folder contains a `.webp` file... this is not supported" or if it uploaded the other files and just failed on that one.  Either way, the folder works now that I've fixed that file
your folder contains a .webp file, and we don’t handle that file extension - that’s why the error shows up
